<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="36.[189,454,1029,1055]" box="[189,454,1029,1055]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,454,1029,1055]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,454,1029,1055]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[188,1399,1078,1218]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="1998" box="[189,398,1078,1104]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="egregia">
<emphasis box="[189,398,1078,1104]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Cheilosia egregia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the single taxon of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov, 2002" authorityName="Barkalov" authorityYear="2002" box="[815,1148,1078,1105]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Rubrocheila">
<emphasis box="[815,959,1078,1104]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Rubrocheila</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Barkalov A. V." box="[966,1148,1078,1105]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="218 - 234" refId="ref48378" refString="Barkalov A. V. 2002. A subgeneric classification of the genus Cheilosia Meigen, 1822 (Diptera, Syrphidae). Entomologicheskoe obozrenie 81: 218 - 234. [In Russian.]" type="journal article" year="2002">Barkalov, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The species is easily distinguished from all congeners by the following combination of characters: abdominal terga orange in anterior ⅔ parts, and black in posterior ⅓, basoflagellomere with a dusky yellow colour and arista with distinct pilosity.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
